<% content_for(:title) { 'Your Personal Job Search HQ' } %>

<%# ─── NAV ─── %>
<nav class="fixed top-0 inset-x-0 z-50 bg-white/80 dark:bg-neutral-950/80 backdrop-blur-xl border-b border-neutral-200/60 dark:border-neutral-800/40">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 h-16 flex items-center justify-between">
    <%= link_to root_path, class: 'flex items-center gap-1.5 text-primary-600' do %>
      <%= inline_svg_tag 'icons/note-filled.svg', class: 'size-6 shrink-0' %>
      <span class="text-xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">JobJournal</span>
    <% end %>

    <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
      <% if authenticated? %>
        <%= link_to dashboard_path, class: 'btn btn-primary' do %>
          <span>Home</span>
          <%= inline_svg_tag 'icons/arrow-right.svg', class: 'size-4 shrink-0' %>
        <% end %>
      <% else %>
        <%= link_to 'Sign In', new_session_path, class: 'btn btn-transparent' %>
        <%= link_to 'Sign Up Free', new_registrations_path, class: 'btn btn-primary' %>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</nav>

<%# ─── HERO ─── %>
<section class="pt-36 md:pt-44 pb-20 md:pb-28 px-6">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
    <h1 class="text-[clamp(2.75rem,6vw,5rem)] font-extrabold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100 leading-[1.08] text-balance">
      Your personal job<br class="hidden sm:block"> search HQ.
    </h1>

    <p class="mt-6 text-[clamp(1.05rem,1.5vw,1.25rem)] text-light max-w-2xl mx-auto text-pretty leading-relaxed">
      A privacy-first web app to help job seekers stay organized, track every lead, application, and interview, and gain insight into their job search journey&mdash;all in one place. No messy spreadsheets. No recruiter dashboards.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-4">
      <% if authenticated? %>
        <%= link_to dashboard_path, class: 'btn btn-primary px-8 py-3 text-base' do %>
          <span>Go to Dashboard</span>
          <%= inline_svg_tag 'icons/arrow-right.svg', class: 'size-5 shrink-0' %>
        <% end %>
      <% else %>
        <%= link_to 'Sign Up Free', new_registrations_path, class: 'btn btn-primary px-8 py-3 text-base' %>
        <%= link_to 'Sign In', new_session_path, class: 'btn btn-secondary btn-muted px-8 py-3 text-base' %>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ─── HERO SCREENSHOT ─── %>
<section class="px-6 pb-24 md:pb-32">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-neutral-200/60 dark:border-neutral-800/30 shadow-xl dark:shadow-none overflow-hidden">
      <%= image_tag 'dashboard.webp', alt: 'JobJournal dashboard showing weekly stats, upcoming interviews, and follow-up suggestions', class: 'w-full h-auto', loading: 'eager' %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ─── THE PROBLEM ─── %>
<section class="py-20 md:py-28 px-6 bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-900/40">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3.5vw,2.75rem)] font-extrabold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100 text-balance leading-tight">
      Spreadsheets weren&rsquo;t built&nbsp;for&nbsp;this.
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-5 text-[clamp(1rem,1.2vw,1.125rem)] text-light leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Searching for jobs is often overwhelming, chaotic, and emotionally draining&mdash;especially when juggling multiple applications, deadlines, and interview processes. And every career blog, coaching platform, and Reddit advice thread preaches the same gospel: &ldquo;just open Excel or Google Sheets and log every lead.&rdquo;
      </p>

      <p>
        But once your search scales, the limitations become obvious. A spreadsheet never reminds you to follow up on applications or interviews. It can&rsquo;t alert you when you forget to apply to a lead you saved last week. It can&rsquo;t offer insights to help you see which sources are actually working. Spreadsheets silo context, scattering interview notes, meeting links, and follow-up reminders across different apps where they&rsquo;re too easily forgotten.
      </p>

      <p>
        They&rsquo;re error-prone and fragile. They lack consistency. They aren&rsquo;t mobile-friendly. There&rsquo;s no sense of context tying leads, notes, and interviews together, and no built-in structure to help you stay motivated. And as your search grows, spreadsheets simply don&rsquo;t scale&mdash;they become harder to navigate, harder to maintain, easier to break, and less useful when you need them most.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ─── THE SOLUTION ─── %>
<section class="py-20 md:py-28 px-6">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3.5vw,2.75rem)] font-extrabold tracking-tight text-primary-600 text-balance leading-tight">
      JobJournal flips that&nbsp;script.
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-5 text-[clamp(1rem,1.2vw,1.125rem)] text-light leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Instead of forcing you to babysit cells, each opportunity is treated as a <strong class="text-normal font-semibold">living record</strong>: timeline-aware suggestions appear automatically on your dashboard; notes are attached to the stage where they belong; helpful insights visualize which sources convert; and universal searching with tags and filters helps you easily find whatever you&rsquo;re looking for, whether it&rsquo;s from yesterday or from 6 months ago.
      </p>

      <p>
        JobJournal features a bird&rsquo;s-eye overview of your activity, along with a customizable weekly application goal, helping you keep track of your progress and stay motivated. And smart suggestions spare you from typing the same job title, company name, source, or location again and again.
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100 font-semibold text-[clamp(1.05rem,1.3vw,1.2rem)]">
        By focusing on workflows rather than rows, JobJournal replaces the brittle spreadsheet paradigm with a purpose-built system that scales from a single dream role to 100 concurrent applications&mdash;without breaking your flow or compromising your privacy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ─── SCREENSHOT: JOB LEADS ─── %>
<section class="px-6 pb-24 md:pb-32">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-neutral-200/60 dark:border-neutral-800/30 shadow-lg dark:shadow-none overflow-hidden">
      <%= image_tag 'job_leads.webp', alt: 'JobJournal job leads page showing a grid of tracked opportunities with tags and statuses', class: 'w-full h-auto', loading: 'lazy' %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ─── WHY JOBJOURNAL ─── %>
<section class="py-20 md:py-28 px-6 bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-900/40">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
    <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3.5vw,2.75rem)] font-extrabold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100 text-balance leading-tight">
      Built for you. Not for&nbsp;companies.
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-[clamp(1rem,1.2vw,1.125rem)] text-light leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <p>
        Unlike recruiter tools or job boards, JobJournal isn&rsquo;t built for companies&mdash;it&rsquo;s built <strong class="text-normal font-semibold">for you</strong>. You stay in control of your journey, your story, and your data.
      </p>

      <p>
        Whether you&rsquo;re actively applying or passively looking, JobJournal is built to support your journey every step of the way&mdash;with clarity, structure, and privacy-first values at its core.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ─── FEATURES ─── %>
<section class="py-20 md:py-28 px-6">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3.5vw,2.75rem)] font-extrabold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100 text-balance leading-tight">
        Core Features
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
      <%# Feature 1: Job Lead Management %>
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800 not-dark:shadow-xs">
        <div class="rounded-xl p-2.5 bg-primary-100/70 dark:bg-primary-900/40 inline-flex mb-4">
          <%= inline_svg_tag 'icons/briefcase.svg', class: 'size-5 text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-500' %>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-normal">Job Lead Management</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-light leading-relaxed">
          Track key details like company, job title, source, salary, and location. Automatically records a timeline of status changes from lead to accepted. Create and reuse custom tags and add unlimited notes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <%# Feature 2: Alerts & Reminders %>
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800 not-dark:shadow-xs">
        <div class="rounded-xl p-2.5 bg-blue-100/70 dark:bg-blue-900/40 inline-flex mb-4">
          <%= inline_svg_tag 'icons/clock.svg', class: 'size-5 text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-500' %>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-normal">Alerts &amp; Reminders</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-light leading-relaxed">
          See upcoming interviews at a glance. Get suggestions to follow up after applications and interviews. Reminders to rate and reflect on past interviews. Highlights stale leads you forgot to apply to.
        </p>
      </div>

      <%# Feature 3: Interview Tracking %>
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800 not-dark:shadow-xs">
        <div class="rounded-xl p-2.5 bg-purple-100/70 dark:bg-purple-900/40 inline-flex mb-4">
          <%= inline_svg_tag 'icons/interview.svg', class: 'size-5 text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-500' %>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-normal">Interview Tracking</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-light leading-relaxed">
          Log interviews with interviewer name, date and time, location, and call URL. Rate how you felt about the interview. Add unlimited notes for prep, debrief, or feedback. Add interviews to your calendar in a single click.
        </p>
      </div>

      <%# Feature 4: Search & Filters %>
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800 not-dark:shadow-xs">
        <div class="rounded-xl p-2.5 bg-amber-100/70 dark:bg-amber-900/40 inline-flex mb-4">
          <%= inline_svg_tag 'icons/search.svg', class: 'size-5 text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-500' %>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-normal">Smart Search &amp; Filters</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-light leading-relaxed">
          Universal search for job leads, interviews, and notes. Filter job leads by tags, status, or active vs. archived. Filter interviews by date. Filter notes by parent type.
        </p>
      </div>

      <%# Feature 5: Insights %>
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800 not-dark:shadow-xs">
        <div class="rounded-xl p-2.5 bg-rose-100/70 dark:bg-rose-900/40 inline-flex mb-4">
          <%= inline_svg_tag 'icons/star.svg', class: 'size-5 text-rose-600 dark:text-rose-500' %>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-normal">Insights</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-light leading-relaxed">
          Track number of job leads, applications, and interviews per week. Set a weekly application goal to boost motivation. Analyze the effectiveness of job sources. See how far each source gets you in the hiring process.
        </p>
      </div>

      <%# Feature 6: Tags & Notes %>
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800 not-dark:shadow-xs">
        <div class="rounded-xl p-2.5 bg-teal-100/70 dark:bg-teal-900/40 inline-flex mb-4">
          <%= inline_svg_tag 'icons/tag.svg', class: 'size-5 text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-500' %>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-normal">Tags &amp; Notes</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-light leading-relaxed">
          Create and reuse custom tags (e.g., &ldquo;remote,&rdquo; &ldquo;dream job,&rdquo; &ldquo;priority&rdquo;). Add unlimited notes for job details, application notes, and company research. Keep everything in context.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ─── PRIVACY ─── %>
<section class="py-20 md:py-28 px-6 bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-900/40">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
    <div class="rounded-full p-4 bg-primary-100/70 dark:bg-primary-900/40 inline-flex mb-6">
      <%= inline_svg_tag 'icons/security.svg', class: 'size-8 text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-500' %>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3.5vw,2.75rem)] font-extrabold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100 text-balance leading-tight">
      Privacy &amp; Security
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-[clamp(1rem,1.2vw,1.125rem)] text-light leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <p>
        Your job search data should be <em>yours alone</em>. That&rsquo;s why JobJournal is <strong class="text-normal font-semibold">privacy-first</strong> by design: all your data stays personal, with no sharing, no tracking, and no analytics dashboards for recruiters.
      </p>

      <p>
        All your data is scoped to your user account. No third-party sharing, no analytics, no tracking, and no recruiter dashboards&mdash;your data stays private. Delete your account and all associated data at any time at the press of a button.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ─── FINAL CTA ─── %>
<section class="py-20 md:py-28 px-6">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
    <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3.5vw,2.75rem)] font-extrabold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100 text-balance leading-tight">
      Stay organized, stay motivated,<br class="hidden sm:block"> and stay private.
    </h2>

    <p class="mt-4 text-[clamp(1rem,1.2vw,1.125rem)] text-light leading-relaxed">
      Free to use. No credit card required.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-4">
      <% if authenticated? %>
        <%= link_to dashboard_path, class: 'btn btn-primary px-8 py-3 text-base' do %>
          <span>Go to Dashboard</span>
          <%= inline_svg_tag 'icons/arrow-right.svg', class: 'size-5 shrink-0' %>
        <% end %>
      <% else %>
        <%= link_to 'Sign Up Free', new_registrations_path, class: 'btn btn-primary px-10 py-3.5 text-base' %>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ─── FOOTER ─── %>
<footer class="py-10 px-6 border-t border-neutral-200/60 dark:border-neutral-800/40">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-4">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5 text-primary-600">
      <%= inline_svg_tag 'icons/note-filled.svg', class: 'size-5 shrink-0' %>
      <span class="text-base font-extrabold tracking-tight">JobJournal</span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-sm text-muted">
      Created with ❤️ by <%= link_to 'Braden Roth', 'https://bradenroth.com', target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener noreferrer', class: 'text-light hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors duration-150' %>
    </p>
  </div>
</footer>
